<table>
  <tr>
   <td>Today, the <strong><a
href=\"http://g.co/play/playbook-androiddevelopers-blog-launch\">Playbook for
Developers</a> </strong>mobile app is now
generally available for Android devices. The app helps you stay up-to-date with
the features and best practices to grow your business on Google Play. Thanks to
all our beta testers over the last six weeks whose feedback helped us tweak and
refine the app in preparation for launch.
<p>
  Here’s how you read and watch content in the Playbook for Developers app:<ul>
<li>Choose topics relating to your business interests to personalize <strong>My
Playbook</strong>   with curated articles and videos from Google and experts
across the web.
<li><strong>Explore</strong>   the in-depth guide to Google’s developer
products, with articles grouped by what you’re trying to do: develop, launch,
engage, grow, and earn.
<li>Take actions on items – complete, share, save, or dismiss them – and read
your <strong>Saved</strong>   articles later, including offline if they’re
written in the app. A data connection will be needed to read articles and videos
from across the web.</li></ul>
   </td>
   <td>
<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://g.co/play/playbook-androiddevelopers-blog-launch\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-aHrPhvmD5PU/V2lsccS9RWI/AAAAAAAADM4/cJNdGCFePssWEvFN5S1Y2huVvghHV2QNQCLcB/s320/Screen%2BShot%2B2016-06-21%2Bat%2B5.27.55%2BPM.png\" /></a></div>
   </td>
  </tr>
</table>
