</p><div class=\"feedflare\">
<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/hsDu?a=Ygv4vn5R7QA:0EB9qnnAnCQ:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/hsDu?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/hsDu?a=Ygv4vn5R7QA:0EB9qnnAnCQ:-BTjWOF_DHI\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/hsDu?i=Ygv4vn5R7QA:0EB9qnnAnCQ:-BTjWOF_DHI\" border=\"0\"></img></a>
</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/blogspot/hsDu/~4/Ygv4vn5R7QA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>") (link ((rel . "edit") (type . "application/atom+xml") (href . "http://www.blogger.com/feeds/6755709643044947179/posts/default/211985356474669534"))) (link ((rel . "self") (type . "application/atom+xml") (href . "http://www.blogger.com/feeds/6755709643044947179/posts/default/211985356474669534"))) (link ((rel . "alternate") (type . "text/html") (href . "http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/blogspot/hsDu/~3/Ygv4vn5R7QA/building-for-billions.html") (title . "Building for Billions"))) (author nil (name nil "Reto Meier") (uri nil "https://plus.google.com/113601876824575481275") (email nil "noreply@blogger.com") (gd:image ((rel . "http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail") (width . "32") (height . "32") (src . "//lh6.googleusercontent.com/--nC4_9HC4lI/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAACg8/wJiYzkAyzlQ/s512-c/photo.jpg")))) (media:thumbnail ((xmlns:media . "http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/") (url . "https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-x5sjb6At2yg/V3WLjDZUTlI/AAAAAAAADSs/uNDvWmzoLcImTAxDZBkVdTKnOcjy-cQbwCLcB/s72-c/IMG_20140917_093824.jpg") (height . "72") (width . "72"))) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://android-developers.blogspot.com/2016/06/building-for-billions.html"))) ("New video tips to help news publishers find success on Google Play" "<p><em>Posted by Tamzin Taylor - Strategic Partner Lead, Google Play</em>
<table>
<tr>
<td>Today we have released a three-part video series ‘<em>Tips for
your news app on Google Play’</em>, where you can find actionable tips
and learn best practices for developing, launching and monetising a high quality
news app. The video series accompanies the recently published <a
href=\"https://play.google.com/store/books/details/Google_Inc_The_News_Publisher_Playbook_for_Android?id=O7T3CwAAQBAJ\">News
Publisher Playbook</a>.
<p>
<a
href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLWz5rJ2EKKc_ElGrEtiEXc83m1SeYu3-Q\">Watch
the video series</a> to learn:<ul>
<li>10 tips on how to design and develop your News app
<li>10 tips to help you launch your News app and start gaining readers
<li>10 tips to engage your readers and monetize your News app</li></ul>
<p>
<!--[Interactive video]  --><iframe width=\"557\" height=\"370\" \" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/KXdQ90llAHg?list=PLWz5rJ2EKKc9Mb16jZJnULoOu6Uavvo2D\" style=\"box-shadow: 3px 10px 18px 1px #999; display: block; margin-bottom:1em; margin-left: 80px;\" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<p>
You can also <a
href=\"https://play.google.com/store/books/details/Google_Inc_The_News_Publisher_Playbook_for_Android?id=O7T3CwAAQBAJ&hl=en_GB\">get
the News Publisher Playbook on the Play Store</a> to help you develop a
successful news mobile strategy on Android. It includes tips on mobile website
optimization, how to create a Google Play Newsstand edition, how to improve your
native app, and more.
<p>
<strong>Give us your feedback</strong>
<p>
Once you’ve checked out the video series, we’d love to hear your feedback so we
can continue to help you find success with and achieve your business objectives.
Leave a comment or a thumbs up, and <a
href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCVHFbqXqoYvEWM1Ddxl0QDg?sub_confirmation=1\">subscribe
to the Android Developers YouTube channel</a>!
<p>
Also, <a
href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLWz5rJ2EKKc_ElGrEtiEXc83m1SeYu3-Q\">check
out our other videos in in the Tips for Success on Google Play series</a>,
including the recent video on <a
href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PfwHq8w9GBc&list=PLWz5rJ2EKKc_ElGrEtiEXc83m1SeYu3-Q&index=11\">10
tips to build an app for billions of users</a>.
<p>
For more best practices to find success on Google Play, <a
href=\"http://g.co/play/playbook-androiddevblogposts-evergreen\">get the new
Playbook for Developers app</a>.
</td>
<td>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
