<div class=\"separator\" style=\"clear: both; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-GYIPLurvUcY/V3GHSZZQYRI/AAAAAAAADSI/xXA-oV7jDNIZAy1XXDpJmbZX1DuwfB6UACLcB/s1600/image00.png\" imageanchor=\"1\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\"><img border=\"0\" src=\"https://3.bp.blogspot.com/-GYIPLurvUcY/V3GHSZZQYRI/AAAAAAAADSI/xXA-oV7jDNIZAy1XXDpJmbZX1DuwfB6UACLcB/s640/image00.png\" /></a></div>

<p>
As an important framework for finding objects in photos and video, Mobile Vision
operation for Android devices is restored in Google Play Services v9.2.
</p>
<p>
This new version of Google Play Services fixes a download issue in Google Play
Services v.9.0 that caused a service outage.  See <a
href=\"https://developers.google.com/vision/release-notes\">release notes</a> for
details.
